column5: i used to own a bunch of reptiles.. used to frequent www.ssnakess.com alot... too bad that site went sour and i got out of the reptile thing used to own a bunch of snakes, chameleons, geckos, frogs, insects
I got a 44" female Sinaloan Milksnake & a monstrous female Emperor Scorpion that is the nastiest critter on earth!  www.herpcentre.com has a great forum & all the info you need.

ahh.. cool i had one of them.. i remember the saying, if red touches black, you're lucky jack (milksnakes - non poisonous) if red touches yellow, you're a dead fellow (coral snakes - poisonous)   i had alot of the common stuff, boa constrictor, ball python, leopard gecko, veiled chameleon, dart frogs, werner's chameleon, giant day gecko, children's python, blood python, kingsnakes, cornsnakes.. and probably some more.. lol
i have three leapord geckos that i'm trying to part with...
